    {
      "id": "sybil_12_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_12",
      "description": "Available now is a museum-grade 2011 BMW M3 (E92) featuring the iconic S65B40 naturally aspirated 4.0L V8. This ZCP Competition Package example is mechanically flawless, having received proactive rod bearing replacement and throttle actuator service. The high-revving powerplant is mated to a crisp 7-speed M-DCT dual-clutch transmission, delivering power to the rear wheels via a variable M differential lock. The chassis exhibits zero fatigue, and the Electronic Damper Control (EDC) provides precise damping across all drive modes. Cosmetically, the Alpine White finish and carbon fiber roof are impeccable, reflecting its climate-controlled storage history. A true collector-grade specimen for the discerning enthusiast.",
